---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="From Mithras to Mass — Sun Worship — Nazaryah"
  description="The Roman Empire did not abandon sun worship when it adopted Christianity — it absorbed Christianity into its existing solar religion."
>
  <div class="sw-wrap">

    <!-- ── HERO ── -->
    <section class="sw-hero">
      <p class="sw-label">&#8213; Sun Worship &#8213;</p>
      <h1 class="sw-title">From Mithras to Mass</h1>
      <p class="sw-sub">
        The Roman Empire did not abandon sun worship when it adopted Christianity — it absorbed Christianity into its existing solar religion.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
    <section class="sw-section">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p>
          Mithraism, the cult of Sol Invictus, and the priesthood of Babylon flowed directly into Papal Rome. The halo, the December 25th birth, the Sun-day Sabbath, the elevated priesthood, the wafer held up to the sun — none of it came from Scripture.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Roman Empire did not abandon sun worship when it adopted Christianity. It absorbed Christianity into its existing solar religion. Constantine did not convert — he consolidated. The result was a new institution that spoke the language of the Messiah while carrying the bones of Mithras.
        </p>
        <p>
          This page traces the unbroken line from the Mithraic temples of imperial Rome to the cathedrals of the Vatican, showing that what the world calls Christianity is, in many of its forms, <em>repackaged sun worship</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── COMING SOON ── -->
    <section class="sw-section sw-section-alt">
      <div class="sw-prose sw-coming-soon">
        <div class="sw-soon-icon">&#9685;</div>
        <h2 class="sw-soon-title">Full Study Coming</h2>
        <p>
          This study is being assembled — covering the cult of Sol Invictus, the Mithraic mystery schools, Constantine's Council of Nicaea, and the specific solar symbols that were carried wholesale into Roman Catholic practice.
        </p>
        <p>
          Return to the <a href="/sun-worship" class="sw-link">Sun Worship hub</a> or read <a href="/sun-worship/the-ancient-lie" class="sw-link">The Ancient Lie</a> for the full historical thread while this page is being built.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── QUOTE ── -->
    <section class="sw-footer-quote">
      <p class="sw-quote-text">"Come out of her, my people, that you be not partakers of her sins, and that you receive not of her plagues."</p>
      <p class="sw-quote-ref">— Revelation 18:4</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .sw-wrap {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0e0904 0%, #1a1208 20%, #160f07 100%);
    color: #f0e0bf;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .sw-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem 3.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #4a3218;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 0%, rgba(180, 100, 20, 0.2), transparent 70%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, #0a0602 0%, #1a1208 100%);
  }

  .sw-label {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    color: #8a6028;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .sw-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .sw-sub {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    color: #c4a46b;
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 580px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .sw-section {
    padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2e1f0d;
  }

  .sw-section-alt {
    background: rgba(10, 6, 2, 0.3);
  }

  .sw-prose {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: #d9c9a8;
  }

  .sw-prose p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .sw-prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .sw-prose em { color: #c4a46b; font-style: italic; }

  .sw-link {
    color: #BA7517;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  .sw-link:hover { color: #d4930f; }

  .sw-coming-soon {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .sw-soon-icon {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: #5a3a10;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .sw-soon-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #c4a46b;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .sw-footer-quote {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #160f07 0%, #0e0904 100%);
  }

  .sw-quote-text {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    font-style: italic;
    color: #c4a46b;
    max-width: 580px;
    margin: 0 auto 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .sw-quote-ref {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: #5a3e1a;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
</style>
